  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this paper, we introduce isoparametric functions and isoparametric hypersurfaces in Finsler manifolds and give the necessary and sufficient conditions for a transnormal function to be isoparametric. We then prove that hyperplanes, Minkowski hyperspheres and <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>⁎</mo></mrow></msup></math> -Minkowski cylinders in a Minkowski space with BH -volume (resp. HT -volume) form are all isoparametric hypersurfaces with one and two distinct constant principal curvatures respectively. Moreover, we give a complete classification of isoparametric hypersurfaces in Randers–Minkowski spaces.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
